cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with tree transducers and their compositions, which are fundamental concepts in formal language theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of computing tree transducer compositions. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as tree transducers are used in logical frameworks such as modal logic and temporal logic. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the membership problem for compositions of tree transducers. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the expressiveness of tree transducer compositions and their relation to programming language semantics.
